<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 1:26PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Floyd and
central Chattooga Counties through 200 PM EDT...
At 126 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Summerville, moving
southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rome, Summerville, Trion, Berryton, Tidings, Armuchee and James H.
Floyd State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
